<task id="016" project="spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Update `SemanticSearchEndpoints.cs` to pass DTO `SearchIndexName` field to resolver</title>
    <phase>B: BFF resolver extension</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>1-2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>013, 014, 015</dependencies>
    <blocks>017</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, api, endpoints, minimal-api</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Tags include `bff-api`; modifies .cs endpoint code at the HTTP boundary. Integration point that wires DTO → service → resolver. ProblemDetails propagation must be correct.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Single-file integration point — all upstream thread-through tasks (013/014/015) must complete first.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Wire the DTO `SearchIndexName` field through `SemanticSearchEndpoints.cs` to the service calls (which were updated in tasks 013/014/015). Verify the ProblemDetails 400 from `INDEX_NOT_ALLOWED` propagates correctly through the endpoint layer to the HTTP response (ADR-019). Existing endpoint-filter authorization (ADR-008) is UNCHANGED.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    BFF developer familiar with `Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/` Minimal-API endpoint registrations and the endpoint-filter authz pattern. Read `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` for the binding pre-merge checklist.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `SemanticSearchEndpoints.cs` reads `request.SearchIndexName` and passes it to the appropriate service call(s). On bad index, the resolver's `INDEX_NOT_ALLOWED` exception/Result surfaces as a 400 ProblemDetails JSON response. End-to-end trace shows the resolved index name in the issued Azure Search URL.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Final integration point of Phase B. Tasks 010-015 delivered the resolver, DTO, appsettings, and three service thread-throughs. This task wires them together at the HTTP boundary so a client request specifying `searchIndexName` routes correctly all the way to Azure Search, and bad values surface as ProblemDetails 400.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/SemanticSearchEndpoints.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/SemanticSearch/SemanticSearchService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/RagService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/RecordSearch/RecordSearchService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1/spec.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec.md FR-BFF-07">Search endpoint MUST thread `SearchIndexName` from request DTO into resolver call. End-to-end acceptance: server log shows resolved index name in the issued Azure Search URL.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec.md NFR-02">Existing endpoint tests pass UNMODIFIED.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec.md NFR-08">400 INDEX_NOT_ALLOWED returns valid ProblemDetails JSON with extension members (ADR-019).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">Minimal-API endpoint pattern — `MapPost(...).WithName(...)` with request body binding.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Endpoint-filter authorization — DO NOT change the existing filter; it stays.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">ProblemDetails JSON for all 4xx responses with `type` URI, `title`, `status`, `detail`, plus extension members.</constraint>
    <constraint source=".claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md">Binding pre-merge checklist for any BFF addition.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-001-bff-minimal-api.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-008-endpoint-filter-authorization.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-019-problem-details.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/api/endpoint-definition.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/api/endpoint-filters.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1/spec.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Endpoint definition" location=".claude/patterns/api/endpoint-definition.md">
        Endpoint reads request body via parameter binding; passes the relevant fields explicitly to the service method. No service-layer model coupling beyond the DTO.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="ProblemDetails propagation" location="ADR-019">
        Service-layer exception (e.g., `IndexNotAllowedException`) is mapped at the endpoint or middleware layer to a 400 ProblemDetails response. The mapping handler should include the rejected value as an extension member.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `SemanticSearchEndpoints.cs` to map current endpoints and how they call the services (`SemanticSearchService`, `RagService`, `RecordSearchService`).</step>
    <step order="2">For each endpoint that binds one of the three updated DTOs, ensure `request.SearchIndexName` is passed through (either as part of the request object, which already flows, or as an explicit parameter — depending on the existing call signature).</step>
    <step order="3">Verify the `INDEX_NOT_ALLOWED` exception/Result from the resolver (task 010) surfaces as a 400 ProblemDetails. This may be via an existing exception-mapping middleware or via an explicit `try/catch` at the endpoint. If neither exists yet, add a minimal exception filter or mapping at the endpoint level that produces ProblemDetails with `type`, `title`, `status: 400`, `detail`, and an extension member naming the rejected index.</step>
    <step order="4">Confirm the existing endpoint-filter authz (ADR-008) is unchanged — no new filters, no removed filters.</step>
    <step order="5">Local run: send a POST with `searchIndexName: "spaarke-file-index"` and verify a BFF log line shows the resolved index name. Capture the log snippet to task notes.</step>
    <step order="6">Run `dotnet build` + `dotnet test`; verify existing endpoint tests pass unmodified.</step>
    <step order="7">Update `TASK-INDEX.md` status: 🔲 → ✅. Update `current-task.md`.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Read existing endpoint registration</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Wire DTO field to service calls; add ProblemDetails mapping if needed</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">Build + local-run smoke test to capture trace</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/SemanticSearchEndpoints.cs</output>
