  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">FR-BFF-07 (final wiring): End-to-end — client sends `searchIndexName`, server log shows the resolved index name in the issued Azure Search URL.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">NFR-08: 400 INDEX_NOT_ALLOWED returns valid ProblemDetails JSON with extension members.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">NFR-02: Existing endpoint tests pass UNMODIFIED.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">ADR-008: Endpoint-filter authz unchanged (verified by code review).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    This task closes the Phase B implementation loop. Task 017 follows with comprehensive unit + integration tests; task 018 deploys.

    If the existing BFF doesn't have a global ProblemDetails exception-mapping middleware, prefer adding the mapping at the endpoint level (smaller blast radius) rather than introducing new middleware in this scope.
  </notes>

